physical_examinations.relevant_findings: At a routine checkup 30 months after gene therapy, lymphocytosis consisting of a monoclonal population of Vg9/Vd1, g/d T cells of mature phenotype was detected. Hepatosplenomegaly developed.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: Between 30 and 34 months after gene therapy, the patient's lymphocyte count rose to 300,000 per cubic millimeter, and a t(6;13) translocation was found that was not detected 30 months after therapy.
